<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FEUDING LAWYERS GET EARFUL FROM ANGRY JUDGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A judge on Thursday lashed out at two Encino lawyers for using the legal system 
to fight a neighborhood dispute that began in one attorney's back yard 
basketball court and escalated to a full-blown Superior Court battle. 
</P>
<P>
"You have by your conduct and by your positions as lawyers embarrassed the bar 
and the judicial system as a whole," Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Marvin D. 
Rowen told attorneys Michael Rubin and Kenneth Schild. "You have subjected the 
whole system to ridicule." 
</P>
<P>
Rowen granted a request for an extension of a temporary restraining order 
sought by Rubin to restrict the times during which the Schild family could use 
the basketball court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
