<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE OF LITHUANIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reading the article "Vilnius: An Exodus From Rebirth" (July 9), I was surprised 
that writer Esther Schrader did not mention that Vilnius was not always the 
capital of Lithuania. 
</P>
<P>
Between 1919 and 1939, Vilnius was a Polish City called Vilno. The capital of 
Lithuania was Kaunas. 
</P>
<P>
The Lithuanians worked very closely with the German occupation forces (after 
1939) and were always in assistance when a ghetto in Poland was eliminated. No 
wonder the Jews are leaving Vilnius. They do not trust the Lithuanians. 
</P>
<P>
BENNO FISCHER 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
