A PICNIC AT HOLLYWOOD BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re: "Life Is a Picnic as Hollywood Bowl Opens" (July 12): Besides those 
(socialites) you listed as being present at the Hollywood Bowl opening, there 
were, to my sure knowledge, Butch, a welder; Scotty, an auto mechanic; Marie, a 
waitress; Deming, a retired cop, and Marty, unemployed but looking. 
</P>
<P>
We brought some beer in a cooler. We were all there, and don't you forget it. 
</P>
<P>
FRED SEIFERS 
</P>
<P>
Downey 
