<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Pacific Symphony has balanced its budget of $4,867,650 for the past season, 
orchestra officials announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The Pacific raised $1,317,000 for its sustaining fund, 30% more than through 
fund-raising efforts last year. Ticket sales provided $2,529,000, an amount 5% 
above the record set last year for ticket sale income. 
</P>
<P>
(Monies from contracted services, such as playing for visiting ballet 
companies, provided the remainder.) 
</P>
<P>
By balancing the budget, the Pacific also will become eligible for a $100,000 
grant from the James Irvine Foundation, contingent upon the foundation's 
receiving an independent audit of the orchestra's budget, which officials 
expect to be completed late summer. 
</P>
