<TEXT>
<P>
Ford Recalls 110,000 Vehicles: Ford will inspect about 110,000 model E- and 
F-Series pickup trucks and, if necessary, replace a snap ring in the 
transmission. In some cases where the snap ring has broken, Ford said, it may 
not be possible to engage the "park" mechanism even though the transmission 
shift control level is in the park position, causing the vehicle to roll when 
parked on an incline. 
