<TEXT>
<P>
Baltimore Sun President Larry Strutton has been named president, publisher and 
chief executive of the Rocky Mountain News, where he began his career 26 years 
ago as a Linotype machinist. 
</P>
<P>
Strutton, 49, succeeds William Fletcher as president. Fletcher, 61, has been 
elected chairman of the Denver newspaper. Strutton was named president of the 
Baltimore Sun in April, 1989. He had been executive vice president of the Los 
Angeles Times since 1986. Times Mirror Co. owns the Baltimore Sun and The 
Times. The News is owned by Scripps Howard. 
