<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Occidental Petroleum Corp.: The Los Angeles-based company said its quarterly 
profit rose 11% to $89 million, despite a $134-million earnings decline in its 
chemical division. 
</P>
<P>
That unit earned $172 million, compared to $306 million a year ago. Sales were 
unchanged at $5.1 billion. The 1990 second-quarter results included an 
after-tax gain of $41 million from selling some domestic oil and gas 
properties. The company attributed the earnings decline in its chemical 
division to lower sale prices throughout the industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
