<TEXT>
<P>
Jacobs Engineering: The Pasadena firm said third-quarter net income rose 39% to 
$3.64 million, even as revenue fell 3% to $221.1 million. The company said the 
income figure reflects continued strength in the industry as a whole and noted 
in particular strong performances in its engineering and consulting services. 
</P>
