<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SCEcorp: The Rosemead parent of Southern California Edison Co. said 
second-quarter income rose 3% to $146 million. 
</P>
<P>
Revenue advanced fractionally to $1.59 billion. The firm said a recent 
California Public Utilities Commission decision shifted some of its earnings to 
the first, second and fourth quarters from the third quarter, with no impact on 
annual earnings. As a result of this change, quarter-to-quarter earnings 
comparisons are distorted. 
</P>
