<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARTISTS' GROUP SETS TWO FUND-RAISERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Coalition for Freedom of Expression is holding two benefit 
programs this weekend as part of its Festival of Freedom. Proceeds from the 
events will go toward the group's efforts on behalf of unrestricted National 
Endowment for the Arts funding. 
</P>
<P>
Tickets for both events are $10. 
</P>
<P>
"Obscene . . . With Merit," a performance and video program with works 
challenging the current restrictions of artists' freedom of expression will be 
held tonight at 8 at West Hollywood's EZTV, 8547 Santa Monica Blvd., (213) 
657-1532. Artists performing or presenting videos include Wendell Jones, John 
Greyson, Chris Robbins, Robert Beck, Azian Nurudin, Catherine Saalfield and Zoe 
Leonard, Sheree Rose, Richard Brennan, David Stanley and Scott Shatt. 
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, also at 8 p.m., several performances grouped under the title "Eye of 
the Storm: Artists Challenge the Obscenity Restrictions, the Religious Right 
and Censorship," will be presented at Venice's Beyond Baroque Literary Arts 
Center, 681 Venice Blvd., (213) 822-3006. Performers include Ayofemi Folayan, 
Robin Podolsky, Janice Porter-Moffett, Alan Pulner, Linda Sibio, Matias 
Viegener and Curtis York. 
</P>
<P>
For information about the Coalition for Freedom of Expression, contact Kathy 
Gronau at (213) 655-5214 or Alan Pulner at (213) 856-0250. 
</P>
</TEXT>
