<TEXT>
<P>
American jockey Steve Cauthen was fined $1,800 by the Jockey Club, the 
governing body of British horse racing, for withdrawing from a race at the last 
minute in May. 
</P>
<P>
Cauthen refused to ride a Pip Payne-trained colt, Nicholas Payne, at Leicester 
after he weighed out. 
</P>
<P>
"I didn't think it was fair of the trainer to book me for that particular 
horse," Cauthen said. "There is no doubt he was a difficult ride -- everybody 
backed me." 
</P>
<P>
Cauthen can appeal the decision. 
</P>
