<P>
BUCKEY JURY RETURNS ONE SEALED VERDICT, STILL DEBATES 7 OTHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The jury in Ray Buckey's second trial told the judge today it has reached a 
verdict on one of eight counts against the former teacher at the McMartin 
Pre-School. 
</P>
<P>
Superior Court Judge Stanley Weisberg told the panelists to resume their talks, 
and the one verdict submitted in a sealed envelope was held in court custody 
until jurors resolve the remaining charges. 
</P>
<P>
The jury has been deliberating for two weeks and heard nearly three days of 
repetition of testimony earlier this week. 
</P>
<P>
Buckey is charged with molesting three young girls who attended his family's 
nursery school in Manhattan Beach in the 1980s. 
</P>
<P>
He and his mother, Peggy McMartin Buckey, were acquitted of 52 molestation 
counts in an earlier trial. But the jury deadlocked on some of the charges 
against Buckey. 
</P>
