<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NAGOYA, Japan 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Toyota Motor Corp. said today it will spend an estimated $1.8 billion to build 
a new assembly plant and two auto parts manufacturing facilities in southern 
and northern Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Toyota said an assembly plant with annual capacity of 200,000 small-sized 
luxury cars will be built in Fukuoka Prefecture on Japan's southern island of 
Kyushu. 
</P>
<P>
The auto parts manufacturing facilities will be located on the northern main 
island of Hokkaido and in the northern part of Honshu main island. 
</P>
<P>
The company said the production facilities will be its first such plants to be 
located outside the Nagoya area in central western Japan. 
